definitions.definition: A ruminant mammal with hooves and often antlers , of the family Cervidae .

subdefinitions.definition: One of the smaller animals of the family Cervidae, distinguished from a moose or elk .
examples: I wrecked my car after a deer ran across the road.

definitions.definition: The meat of such an animal, obtained through the process of hunting or from specialized deer farms; venison .
examples: Oh, I've never had deer before.

definitions.definition: Any animal , especially a quadrupedal mammal as opposed to a bird, fish, etc.
definitions.label_groups: countable ; obsolete , except in the phrase "small deer"

main_definition: ( countable ) A ruminant mammal with hooves and often antlers , of the family Cervidae .
secondary_definitions: ( uncountable ) The meat of such an animal, obtained through the process of hunting or from specialized deer farms; venison .
